A:
Jack can clean a yacht in 12 hours. He finishes two-thirds of the work. The remaining portion of the work is done by Jill, whose rate of cleaning is just 5% of what Jack can do. So, Jill can clean a yacht in 12/3 * 5% = 22 hours. So the answer is (c).

